other_tests.findings: Urine-dipstick results of 1+ blood and 3+ protein; 0 to 3 nondysmorphic red cells and 0 to 4 white cells per high-power field; fatty casts were seen. Urinary sodium level was 53 mmol per liter, and urine creatinine level was 37 mg per deciliter, with a calculated fractional excretion of sodium of 12%.
Enlarged kidneys (measuring 12 to 14 cm) with increased echogenicity but no hydronephrosis.

Pathological analysis revealed collapsing glomerulopathy, associated acute tubular injury, mild diffuse interstitial inflammation, and approximately one third of the glomeruli showed collapsing lesions.
Urine volume of 950 ml and total protein excretion of 22 g.
Serum creatinine level of 1.8 mg per deciliter and a urine volume of more than 2 liters.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Improvements noted with serum creatinine level decreasing to 1.3 mg per deciliter approximately 1 year after hospitalization.
